 converge in the top half of the photo.\" title=\"IMG_2272\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" loading=\"eager\"></a></p><p>Photo submitted by Greg Furry, “This is a vertical panorama from my first lap at&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.in.gov/dnr/parklake/2972.htm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Potato Creek State Park</a>.&nbsp;<span>The </span>Northern Indiana Mountain Bike Association groomed the 7 mile trail for the first time this year.”</p><div><p>We always love seeing photos from where you are riding and are happy to share them with our readers around&nbsp;the world here on the Pic Of The Day. Send in your pics&nbsp;with a description&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:kristi@bikerumor.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">here</a>.</p><p>*Please note that public spaces and parks may have restrictions or be closed to the public due to COVID-19, please check before heading out.</p></div></div></article></div></div>","author":"Kristi Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"c8f5c5b80dffd992cf349cbbd88c4524e30da83bdcbc211aa9407d3b91978230","category":"Cycling"}